article.description: Joel Bolomboy had 15 points, 10 rebounds and three blocks on Thursday night, and Weber State pulled away late in the first half for a 90-47 win over NAIA Antelope Valley.
article.headline: Bolomboy, Weber State beat Antelope Valley 90-47
article.linkText: Bolomboy, Weber State beat Antelope Valley 90-47
article.story: OGDEN, Utah -- Joel Bolomboy had 15 points, 10 rebounds and three blocks on Thursday night, and Weber State pulled away late in the first half for a 90-47 win over NAIA Antelope Valley. Jeremy Senglin had 16 points to lead the Wildcats and made 3 of 4 from 3-point range. Richaud Gittens added 14 points for Weber State (1-2), which shot 13 of 23 from long range and 56.9 percent overall. Antelope Valley started the game with a 9-3 lead. Weber State answered with a 35-7 run and led by no less than 17 from there. The Wildcats had their largest lead at 90-45 just before Josh Sanchez's dunk for the Pioneers capped the scoring. Sanzhez had 18 points on 8-of-14 shooting and Joe McNiff added 9, going 3 of 4 from 3-point range. The rest of the Pioneers shot 7 of 38.
